---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Dominica Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/dominica/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Saint Lucia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/saint-lucia' },
  { title: 'Martinique for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Guadeloupe for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'dominicaFit', header: 'Dominica Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,350-1,930/mo', dominicaFit: 'Essential' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,580-2,255/mo', dominicaFit: 'Essential' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,215-1,735/mo', dominicaFit: 'Essential' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,130-1,615/mo', dominicaFit: 'Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XCD$1,215-1,930', annual: 'XCD$14,580-23,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XCD$1,665-2,575', annual: 'XCD$19,980-30,900' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XCD$2,240-3,450', annual: 'XCD$26,880-41,400' },
  { category: 'Local Clinic Visit', monthly: 'XCD$150-350/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XCD$50,000-150,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Dominica 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Dominica. Nature Island beauty, eco-tourism, affordable CBI, and coverage for adventurous retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Dominica"
  subheadline="Dominica offers the Nature Island experience with rainforests, hot springs, waterfalls, and eco-tourism—plus affordable citizenship by investment for adventurous, nature-loving retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/dominica-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Dominica</h2>
  <p>
    Dominica offers the "Nature Island" experience—365 rivers, boiling lake, rainforest hikes, whale watching, and hot springs. Least developed of Eastern Caribbean with authentic eco-tourism. Affordable citizenship by investment attracts budget-conscious passport seekers. Not beach-focused but nature paradise.
  </p>

  <p>
    Roseau is the small capital. Portsmouth in north has Ross University. Calibishie offers stunning northeast coast. Population only ~72,000—very small. Martinique and Guadeloupe (French, excellent hospitals) are 30-40 minutes by ferry/flight. Miami 4+ hours.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; French islands backup essential</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English; French Creole spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> XCD$4,000-8,000/month (~$1,500-3,000 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical rainforest; wet; hurricane risk</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Eco-focused; rugged; authentic</li>
      <li><strong>CBI:</strong> Most affordable Caribbean citizenship</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Dominica Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Dominica healthcare is very limited—Princess Margaret Hospital in Roseau is main facility but basic. Limited specialists. Hurricane Maria (2017) damaged infrastructure significantly. Complex conditions require evacuation to Martinique (30 minutes) or Guadeloupe (40 minutes)—both French with excellent hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    French islands provide crucial backup. Martinique's CHU Fort-de-France and Guadeloupe's CHU Pointe-à-Pitre offer French-quality care very close by. International insurance covering French territories essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">French Islands Are Lifeline</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Martinique and Guadeloupe (French departments) are just 30-40 minutes away with excellent healthcare. Much closer than Miami. Insurance covering French territories is absolutely essential for Dominica residence. Don't underestimate healthcare limitations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Dominica residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship by Investment</h3>
  <p>
    Most affordable Caribbean CBI—$100,000 donation for single applicant. Dominica passport provides visa-free travel to 140+ countries including Schengen.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Available through investment or extended residence. Lower threshold than citizenship.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Visa extensions available for testing the waters before committing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Dominica:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> French islands coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane:</strong> Evacuation essential during season</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Dominica</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with strong French territory (Martinique, Guadeloupe) coverage essential. Don't rely on local healthcare for anything serious. Include helicopter/boat evacuation given island geography.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Dominica, French territory evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Dominica</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Europe/Americas network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>French coverage:</strong> Martinique/Guadeloupe essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation focus:</strong> Island evacuation coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Dominica with French territory access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Dominica (XCD ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>French islands nearby:</strong> Close, excellent backup</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable CBI:</strong> Cheapest Caribbean citizenship</li>
    <li><strong>Low daily costs:</strong> Very affordable living</li>
    <li><strong>Consider health:</strong> Rugged terrain challenging for some seniors</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Eco-Adventure Retiree, 65</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Nature lover. Very active.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with French territory coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,400/month (~$520). Adventure paradise; Martinique backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Budget Passport Seeker, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month. CBI for travel. Part-time residence.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with worldwide coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,700/month (~$630). Affordable CBI; global mobility.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Diving Enthusiast, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month. Calibishie coast. Whale watching.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with diving coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,350/month (~$500). Underwater paradise; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Dominica suitable for less mobile seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Challenging—rugged terrain, steep roads, limited accessibility. Many attractions require hiking. Not recommended for mobility-limited retirees. Best for active, adventurous seniors who can handle rough conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about Hurricane Maria damage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Recovering—Hurricane Maria (2017) was devastating. Infrastructure rebuilt but some areas still affected. Climate resilient construction now prioritized. Hurricane risk real—consider seasonal evacuation or travel.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is Dominica CBI cheapest?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Less developed, smaller economy, fewer tourists. Dominica uses CBI funds for hurricane recovery and development. Good passport but island is simpler than competitors. Value option for passport seekers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Don't confuse with Dominican Republic?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Common confusion—Dominica (small Eastern Caribbean nature island) vs Dominican Republic (large Spanish-speaking country sharing Hispaniola with Haiti). Very different destinations. Dominica is tiny, English-speaking, nature-focused.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Dominica coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Dominica healthcare is very limited—French island evacuation coverage essential. Terrain challenging for less mobile seniors. Always verify current requirements.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
